down, you’d cry again.

151
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:09,769
Well, it’s because

152
00:10:10,776 --> 00:10:11,944
I really thought

153
00:10:11,944 --> 00:10:15,791
you were just a clingy baby
but I realized the reason was,

154
00:10:16,574 --> 00:10:18,790
you wanted me to carry you so

155
00:10:19,245 --> 00:10:22,832
you could watch everything
happening around you, always observing.

156
00:10:24,498 --> 00:10:28,586
Because of course, if you
were just left in the crib, right,

157
00:10:28,586 --> 00:10:32,965
all you’d see were the
ceiling and the walls.

158
00:10:33,924 --> 00:10:37,678
Oh, my child, even
when you were young,

159
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:42,350
it’s like you were already
ready to face the world and

160
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:48,647
I’m so happy because you
grew up smart and brave.

161
00:10:50,405 --> 00:10:52,851
It’s really amazing to think

162
00:10:53,883 --> 00:10:55,509
that now, you’ve
grown so much and

163
