273
00:17:41,211 --> 00:17:42,229
You too.

274
00:17:42,254 --> 00:17:43,284
Thank God.

275
00:17:43,380 --> 00:17:44,773
And by the way, thank you

276
00:17:44,798 --> 00:17:47,301
for your terrific
influence on my son here.

277
00:17:47,301 --> 00:17:49,511
He’s doing fantastic in school.

278
00:17:49,964 --> 00:17:51,708
Uh, yes, Uncle.

279
00:17:52,014 --> 00:17:53,056
Anything for Pat.

280
00:17:54,349 --> 00:17:55,726
You’re very kind, Grace.

281
00:17:56,310 --> 00:17:58,047
So, let’s eat.

282
00:17:58,437 --> 00:17:59,437
Sit. Sit.

283
00:18:15,537 --> 00:18:17,623
So how are your parents, Grace?

284
00:18:18,763 --> 00:18:21,891
Oh, um, I just live with my dad.

285
00:18:22,002 --> 00:18:23,879
My mom passed
away when I was 13.

286
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:27,316
Dad, uh, remember I told you
about Grace’s parents, right?

287
00:18:27,341 --> 00:18:28,467
Sorry, sorry.

288
00:18:28,467 --> 00:18:29,676
It just slipped my mind.

289
00:18:29,802 --> 00:18:30,886
It’s okay, Uncle.

290
00:18:31,470 --> 00:18:32,805
So you live with your father?

291
00:18:34,431 --> 00:18:36,241
If you don’t mind,
what does he do?

292
00:18:36,266 --> 00:18:37,977
He owns a printing
press company.

293
00:18:38,053 --> 00:18:39,066
Wow.

294
00:18:39,436 --> 00:18:40,229
Salute to him.

295
00:18:40,229 --> 00:18:41,989
A single father
and a businessman.

296
00:18:43,190 --> 00:18:46,360
And he successfully raised a
beautiful and smart daughter.

297
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:51,365
I need to invite him for a
whiskey night one of these days

298
00:18:52,115 --> 00:18:55,202
So we can talk business and all
about business-minded people.

299
00:18:56,119 --> 00:18:57,156
Sure.

300
00:18:57,412 --> 00:18:58,427
You know,

301
00:18:59,456 --> 00:19:00,477
my family,

302
00:19:01,333 --> 00:19:02,835
we weren’t always this well-off.

303
00:19:02,860 --> 00:19:04,987
My father was a
small-time businessman.

304
00:19:05,546 --> 00:19:07,798
He sold steel for construction.

305
00:19:07,798 --> 00:19:09,091
And I was his assistant.

306
00:19:10,217 --> 00:19:11,385
I looked up to him.

307
00:19:11,969 --> 00:19:15,222
He taught me the value of
hard work and determination.

308
00:19:16,014 --> 00:19:19,685
That’s why I worked hard
to reach my current status.

309
00:19:19,685 --> 00:19:21,228
It’s because of his teachings.

310
00:19:21,937 --> 00:19:24,439
And I’m passing on
those lessons to Pat here

311
00:19:24,439 --> 00:19:28,151
so he’ll work hard even if he
didn’t experience our hardships.

312
00:19:29,528 --> 00:19:31,467
Success is sweeter

313
00:19:32,281 --> 00:19:33,615
when it’s earned
through hard work.

314
00:19:33,615 --> 00:19:34,792
Right, son?

315
00:19:34,935 --> 00:19:35,935
Yes, Dad.

316
00:19:36,902 --> 00:19:38,553
That’s why I’m so proud of him.

317
00:19:38,579 --> 00:19:40,348
His improvement in school is

318
00:19:41,415 --> 00:19:42,415
dramatic.

319
00:19:43,208 --> 00:19:44,710
And that’s thanks to you, Grace.

320
00:19:46,461 --> 00:19:48,505
Actually, I didn’t
just invite you here

321
00:19:48,505 --> 00:19:50,173
for a delicious dinner, Grace.

322
00:19:50,173 --> 00:19:52,217
I wanted to give you
something special.

323
00:19:53,343 --> 00:19:55,929
Something that would show
you how much I appreciate

324
00:19:55,929 --> 00:19:57,431
what you’ve done for my son.

325
00:20:03,687 --> 00:20:05,647
I want you, Grace,

326
00:20:06,899 --> 00:20:08,108
to go with Pat

327
00:20:08,984 --> 00:20:11,320
to study at Boston University.

328
00:20:11,320 --> 00:20:13,280
I’ll cover all the expenses.

329
00:20:13,496 --> 00:20:14,464
Dad,

330
00:20:14,489 --> 00:20:15,532
isn’t that a bit,

331
00:20:16,366 --> 00:20:17,676
sudden? I mean,

332
00:20:17,701 --> 00:20:19,202
- Grace has to think about it.
