00:33:33,705 --> 00:33:35,998
Sorry, sorry. I disturbed
you with my call.

537
00:33:37,281 --> 00:33:38,309
Wait a moment, my child.

538
00:33:38,334 --> 00:33:40,878
You mentioned STIC?

539
00:33:41,638 --> 00:33:43,640
Why? Are you going
to study abroad?

540
00:33:46,718 --> 00:33:47,443
Child.

541
00:33:47,468 --> 00:33:49,595
If you want, you can just
study here in Australia,

542
00:33:49,595 --> 00:33:51,264
the schools here are good.

543
00:33:51,767 --> 00:33:54,686
Then I already mentioned
that to your Uncle Greg because

544
00:33:54,711 --> 00:33:57,798
he has lots of contacts here
who can help you. That’s for sure.

545
00:33:58,649 --> 00:34:00,734
And then, won’t
we be together too?

546
00:34:01,315 --> 00:34:03,025
I want to study in the US.

547
00:34:03,168 --> 00:34:04,377
Not in Australia anymore.

548
00:34:06,779 --> 00:34:08,030
Papa and I can manage.

549
00:34:10,867 --> 00:34:11,909
Is that so? Okay.

550
00:34:12,285 --> 00:34:13,536
Okay. Sorry.

551
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:15,788
I just got excited.

552
00:34:16,249 --> 00:34:18,293
Ah, Ma. I have to go.

553
00:34:18,708 --> 00:34:20,501
I’m really sorry. I forgot

554
00:34:20,501 --> 00:34:22,670
that it’s 10:50 a.m.
here in Australia.

555
00:34:22,670 --> 00:34:25,465
Isn’t it more advanced
here than in the Philippines?

556
00:34:25,673 --> 00:34:26,673
Sorry again.

557
00:34:28,926 --> 00:34:29,926
Bye.

558
00:34:42,200 --> 00:34:44,744
7:50 a.m. in the Philippines.

559
00:34:46,461 --> 00:34:48,338
10:50 a.m. in Australia.

560
00:34:51,324 --> 00:34:52,325
Time zones.

561
00:34:52,876 --> 00:34:54,844
Look at the time
here in the Philippines.

562
00:34:54,869 --> 00:34:56,496
It's 12:00 p.m.

563
00:34:56,496 --> 00:34:59,332
While in Australia,
it's already 3:00 pm.

564
00:34:59,332 --> 00:35:01,372
Because of daylight
savings, Australia is

565
00:35:01,396 --> 00:35:03,795
three hours ahead
compared to the Philippines.

566
00:35:04,839 --> 00:35:08,342
Only one exam is used
when taking the STIC.

567
00:35:08,691 --> 00:35:12,106
It’s done at the same
time and on the same day.

568
00:35:12,131 --> 00:35:14,884
So if the exam is at
9:00 a.m. in Australia.

569
00:35:15,598 --> 00:35:17,433
6:00 a.m. for us here?

570
00:35:18,669 --> 00:35:19,535
Correct.

571
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:20,561
So what will happen is,

572
00:35:20,561 --> 00:35:22,688
I’ll take the exam
first in Australia

573
00:35:22,688 --> 00:35:26,275
then I’ll send the answers
before the exam starts here.

574
00:35:26,300 --> 00:35:29,403
Would it be too expensive if
you only sent the answers to us?

575
00:35:29,788 --> 00:35:32,850
Who said you’d be the only
ones benefiting from my answers?

576
00:35:34,308 --> 00:35:35,727
With what we’re going to do,

577
00:35:35,752 --> 00:35:39,338
the whole Philippines can
benefit from the STIC answers.

578
00:35:39,831 --> 00:35:40,940
But Lin,

579
00:35:40,965 --> 00:35:43,676
how are you supposed to
get the answers for the exam?

580
00:35:44,961 --> 00:35:46,016
Memorization.

581
00:35:46,763 --> 00:35:50,016
I’ll memorize all the answers
then I’ll send them to you.

582
00:35:50,417 --> 00:35:51,824
Didn’t you already
take the exam?

583
00:35:52,635 --> 00:35:54,303
Can you memorize all of that?

584
00:35:54,570 --> 00:35:56,925
I can, if I have enough time.

585
00:35:57,390 --> 00:35:59,142
I tested it with
the remaining time

586
00:35:59,167 --> 00:36:01,336
I was able to memorize
half of the exam.

587
00:36:01,700 --> 00:36:02,743
That means,

588
00:36:03,437 --> 00:36:05,106
I can’t do this alone.

589
00:36:07,262 --> 00:36:09,014
Someone has to help me.

590
00:36:09,661 --> 00:36:13,457
And I have no assurance that this
will be the only exam in Pat’s batch.

591
00:36:14,282 --> 00:36:15,291
I see.

592
00:36:16,063 --> 00:36:17,815
So you need someone else.

593
00:36:20,580 --> 00:36:22,582
Who else is as smart as you?

594
00:36:34,760 --> 00:36:38,306
Your x-ray shows that the
spaces in your spine are thinning.

595
00:36:38,806 --> 00:36:40,224
So every time you move,

596
00:36:40,683 --> 00:36:44,145
your bones rub against each other,
causing your pain and discomfort.

597
00:36:44,835 --> 00:36:47,567
This is what we call spinal stenosis.

598
00:36:48,608 --> 00:36:49,526
So, doc,

599
00:36:49,551 --> 00:36:52,169
is there a treatment or
medicine that needs to be done?

600
00:36:52,482 --> 00:36:54,082
Given how severe it is,

601
00:36:54,107 --> 00:36:56,007
the best option I would
recommend your mom

602
00:36:56,032 --> 00:36:58,492
to help her get back
to her normal activities

603
00:36:58,701 --> 00:36:59,750
is surgery.

604
00:37:00,411 --> 00:37:01,095
Doc,

605
00:37:01,120 --> 00:37:03,593
maybe we can
manage with medicine?

606
00:37:04,040 --> 00:37:06,584
Like herbal
remedies? Or maybe...

607
00:37:07,376 --> 00:37:08,376
massage?

608
00:37:08,920 --> 00:37:10,213
Sad to say, ma'am.

609
00:37:10,547 --> 00:37:11,894
There’s no medicine for this.

610
00:37:12,876 --> 00:37:14,544
If we don’t operate on her,

611
00:37:15,011 --> 00:37:17,138
it could potentially
get worse over time.

612
00:37:19,055 --> 00:37:20,055
Ah, Doc.

613
00:37:22,141 --> 00:37:23,476
The problem is,

614
00:37:24,111 --> 00:37:26,613
we don’t have
money for the surgery.

615
00:37:28,981 --> 00:37:30,056
- If…
- Alright, Doc.

616
00:37:31,400 --> 00:37:32,985
Whatever the best option is,

617
00:37:33,861 --> 00:37:34,917
that’s what we’ll do.

618
00:37:35,571 --> 00:37:36,571
Alright.

619
00:37:42,787 --> 00:37:44,622
I don’t understand you

620
00:37:44,622 --> 00:37:48,542
why you agreed with that
doctor that I should have surgery.

621
00:37:48,947 --> 00:37:50,782
You know those doctors,

622
00:37:51,368 --> 00:37:54,371
all they do is make
us spend money.

623
00:37:55,091 --> 00:37:56,217
I even know someone

624
00:37:56,217 --> 00:37:59,011
who just took herbal
medicinal drinks.

625
00:37:59,011 --> 00:38:00,638
It cured their

626
00:38:01,222 --> 00:38:02,233
liver disease.

627
00:38:02,597 --> 00:38:03,532
Ma,

628
00:38:03,557 --> 00:38:05,559
what’s the point of
consulting doctors

629
00:38:05,559 --> 00:38:07,425
if we’re not going
to listen to them?

630
00:38:07,603 --> 00:38:10,398
They’re the experts. They
know what they’re doing.

631
00:38:10,862 --> 00:38:11,862
Child.

632
00:38:14,151 --> 00:38:16,195
Where will we get money

633
00:38:16,654 --> 00:38:17,697
for the surgery?

634
00:38:18,101 --> 00:38:19,603
We have no money.

635
00:38:19,965 --> 00:38:23,321
And then you won’t even
let me take laundry jobs.

636
00:38:23,346 --> 00:38:24,374
So, how?

637
00:38:24,684 --> 00:38:26,247
- Ouch!
- There! Ma!

638
00:38:26,288 --> 00:38:28,582
- Ouch!
- Go slow, just take it easy.

639
00:38:28,582 --> 00:38:29,582
Ouch!

640
00:38:29,625 --> 00:38:30,126
Ow, ow!

641
00:38:30,126 --> 00:38:30,643
Wait, wait.

642
00:38:30,668 --> 00:38:31,727
Ouch!

643
00:38:31,752 --> 00:38:32,852
It hurts!

644
00:38:33,112 --> 00:38:33,938
Oh, there, Ma, look.

645
00:38:33,963 --> 00:38:35,965
Wait! Just wait a second!

646
00:38:37,341 --> 00:38:38,363
- Ma!
- It hurts!

647
00:38:38,884 --> 00:38:40,011
My God! My God!

648
00:38:40,928 --> 00:38:41,928
It hurts!

649
00:38:42,346 --> 00:38:43,346
It hurts!

650
00:38:45,099 --> 00:38:46,200
Are you okay now?

651
00:38:46,225 --> 00:38:47,225
Okay.

652
00:38:47,435 --> 00:38:48,435
I’m okay now.

653
00:38:49,186 --> 00:38:50,186
I’m okay now.

654
00:38:52,398 --> 00:38:53,398
Ma,

655
00:38:54,388 --> 00:38:56,001
you know, I need to find a job

656
00:38:56,027 --> 00:38:58,112
so we can save up
for your back surgery.

657
00:39:01,157 --> 00:39:02,575
And what about your studies?

658
00:39:05,161 --> 00:39:06,595
Ma, we don’t really
have a choice.

659
00:39:06,620 --> 00:39:07,680
No,

660
00:39:07,705 --> 00:39:08,998
Tristan. No.

661
00:39:10,207 --> 00:39:12,793
That could ruin your schooling.

662
00:39:12,900 --> 00:39:16,589
Son, just one more
year and you’ll graduate.

663
00:39:17,423 --> 00:39:19,842
All I need is to rest.

664
00:39:19,842 --> 00:39:21,028
That’s it.

665
00:39:21,053 --> 00:39:24,467
Then I’ll be the
one to find a job.

666
00:39:24,654 --> 00:39:25,865
- I’ll do it.
- Ma!

667
00:39:25,890 --> 00:39:27,349
Why are you so stubborn?

668
00:39:29,185 --> 00:39:30,978
Do you want to make
your condition worse?

669
00:39:31,564 --> 00:39:33,331
Don’t you feel
sorry for yourself?

670
00:39:35,024 --> 00:39:36,108
You can’t even stand up.

671
00:39:36,108 --> 00:39:38,027
You can barely
lean properly, Ma.

672
00:39:50,706 --> 00:39:51,706
Ma,

673
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:54,335
my decision is final.

674
00:39:55,419 --> 00:39:56,587
Please don’t stop me.

675
00:39:58,005 --> 00:40:01,258
My life is less important to
me than your life is to me.

676
00:40:03,302 --> 00:40:05,137
So please, Ma, don’t
be stubborn anymore.

677
00:40:29,411 --> 00:40:30,412
Hi, Lin.

678
00:40:34,583 --> 00:40:36,377
Why did you come by?

679
00:40:38,003 --> 00:40:40,297
Is there a problem
with our plan?

680
00:40:45,845 --> 00:40:47,972
Lin, I’m really sorry.

681
00:40:49,807 --> 00:40:51,809
And I’ve missed you a lot.

682
00:40:53,811 --> 00:40:55,020
Like, a lot.

683
00:40:58,095 --> 00:40:59,471
It’s okay, Grace.

684
00:41:00,276 --> 00:41:02,236
We already talked
earlier, right?

685
00:41:14,456 --> 00:41:15,456
But,

686
00:41:17,251 --> 00:41:18,377
it’s different.

687
00:41:20,744 --> 00:41:22,412
We’re not close anymore.

688
00:41:24,412 --> 00:41:27,457
And I want us to be okay
like how we were before.

689
00:41:27,482 --> 00:41:28,482
And...

690
00:41:29,763 --> 00:41:33,434
I really hope that you’ve
forgiven me for what I did last sem.

691
00:41:36,478 --> 00:41:37,479
That’s nothing.

692
00:41:38,564 --> 00:41:40,024
We all have our reasons.

693
00:41:40,483 --> 00:41:41,859
And we all have our mistakes.

694
00:41:43,986 --> 00:41:45,112
That’s over now, Grace.

695
00:41:47,907 --> 00:41:48,952
Thanks, Lin.

696
00:41:50,724 --> 00:41:51,770
And, yes,

697
00:41:52,912 --> 00:41:55,372
I have learned from
my past mistakes.

698
00:41:58,000 --> 00:42:00,419
Which is why I am also here.

699
00:42:01,562 --> 00:42:03,397
Honestly, I'm really
concerned about you

700
00:42:03,422 --> 00:42:05,549
with this new cheating
scheme that we're planning.

701
00:42:05,966 --> 00:42:08,510
I don't want you to get
in trouble like last time.

702
00:42:10,095 --> 00:42:12,181
I'm okay now, don’t
worry about me.

703
00:42:13,036 --> 00:42:14,036
All is well.

704
00:42:15,476 --> 00:42:16,727
Okay, but

705
00:42:17,230 --> 00:42:18,773
I can't help but wonder,

706
00:42:18,798 --> 00:42:20,842
why do you want to
go through that again?

707
00:42:23,776 --> 00:42:25,194
Let's just say that

708
00:42:25,986 --> 00:42:27,696
I really need the
money right now.

709
00:42:29,740 --> 00:42:30,963
Because,

710
00:42:30,988 --> 00:42:33,157
I don’t want to keep
relying on other people.

711
00:42:36,747 --> 00:42:37,747
Actually,

712
00:42:39,156 --> 00:42:41,116
I’m doing all of this for Dad.

713
00:42:42,169 --> 00:42:43,295
He deserves more.

714
00:42:43,295 --> 00:42:44,505
He deserves better.

715
00:42:45,798 --> 00:42:47,049
He’s been through
too much hardship.

716
00:42:52,798 --> 00:42:53,798
Okay.

717
00:42:55,432 --> 00:42:56,558
Anyway, sis,

718
00:42:57,103 --> 00:42:58,730
no matter what happens,

719
00:43:00,503 --> 00:43:02,964
I'm just always
here for you, okay?

720
00:43:05,442 --> 00:43:06,443
Thanks, sis.

721
00:43:10,489 --> 00:43:11,489
So, here.

722
00:43:12,483 --> 00:43:16,112
So, here are the following
candidates that I have for our plan.

723
00:43:22,322 --> 00:43:23,330
Bank?

724
00:43:25,129 --> 00:43:26,463
What are you doing here?

725
00:43:30,386 --> 00:43:32,805
Aren’t you making money
from leaking exam answers?

726
00:43:35,306 --> 00:43:36,473
Teach me.

727
00:43:41,395 --> 00:43:43,230
- Hey!
- Ouch!

728
00:43:43,689 --> 00:43:45,232
Ouch, son!

729
00:43:45,607 --> 00:43:47,318
My God, I think I’m dying.

730
00:43:47,318 --> 00:43:48,819
If Bank isn’t part of our plan,

731
00:43:48,819 --> 00:43:50,487
the plan won’t push through.

732
00:43:50,487 --> 00:43:51,487
You know that.

733
00:43:54,041 --> 00:43:55,209
We’re going to Australia

734
00:43:55,565 --> 00:43:57,317
to take the STIC exam.

735
00:43:57,342 --> 00:43:58,345
So, Bank,

736
00:43:58,370 --> 00:43:59,847
you memorize the first half

737
00:43:59,872 --> 00:44:00,581
and then,

738
00:44:00,581 --> 00:44:02,207
Lin gets the second half.

739
00:44:02,207 --> 00:44:03,892
We have a contract signing here

740
00:44:03,917 --> 00:44:05,669
and all meetings are recorded.

741
00:44:06,096 --> 00:44:08,769
No one will tell on anyone
because you’re already accomplices.

742
00:44:11,241 --> 00:44:12,943
Why did you do
that to us, Pat, huh?

743
00:44:12,968 --> 00:44:14,386
Why did you do that to us?

744
00:44:14,386 --> 00:44:15,220
No, come on, guys.

745
00:44:15,220 --> 00:44:16,725
You’re really going
to believe him?

746
00:44:16,764 --> 00:44:17,965
He's just stressed out.

747
00:44:20,186 --> 00:44:22,290
Bank, just focus on your mom.

748
00:44:23,020 --> 00:44:24,752
I’ll take care of the STIC.

749
00:44:25,814 --> 00:44:27,066
You’ll still get your share.

750
00:44:27,900 --> 00:44:28,940
Thanks, Lin.

751
00:44:29,651 --> 00:44:30,736
But you and I both know

752
00:44:30,736 --> 00:44:33,105
that you can’t memorize
the whole STIC exam.
